HEADWORD: Nidus
<hw>Ni"dus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>nidi</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L. See <er>Nidi</er>,
<er>Nest</er>.]</ety> <def>A nest: a repository for the eggs of birds,
insects, etc.; a breeding place; esp., the place or substance where
parasites or the germs of a disease effect lodgment or are
developed.</def>⟦br⟧
